        "title": "How can I return a class in enum?",
        "body": "<p>I have a enum called scenes and some classes like game and menu, I get class of the enum using id how can I do that? thats all I need. sorry my english is bad.<\/p>\n<p>EDIT:<\/p>\n<p>this is my code<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>public enum Scenes {\n    \n    MENU(1, &quot;Menu&quot;),\n    GAME(2, &quot;Game&quot;);\n    \n    public static int Scene = 1;\n    \n    private int id;\n    private String name;\n    \n    private Scenes (int id, String name) {\n        this.id = id;\n        this.name = name;\n    }\n\n    public int getId() {\n        return id;\n    }\n\n    public String getName() {\n        return name;\n    }\n    \n}\n\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
